post_text:
Santa Barbara Unified educators kicked off the 2020/21 school year with inspirational words from Dr. Jeff Duncan Andrade, a San Francisco State University professor who founded the Roses in Concrete school in Oakland. About 900 school leaders, teachers, counselors, administrators and other certificated staff attended the webinar before heading into a day of professional development and prep.
Dr. Duncan Andrade told the crowd: “As you all start this school year, I really encourage you to think hard about who among the young people in your community are the most vulnerable. Those have to be folks that you flood your energy with. It’s not a zero sum game. If you are really investing in the most vulnerable and wounded ones, that has a ripple effect. What I’m encouraging us to do is seek solitary with the most wounded ones. How do you take care of, support, invest in those who need us the most. When those folks start to rise, everyone rises.”
#educatorschangelives
#educatorsmakeadifference

post_text:
Tonight, the Santa Barbara Unified School District Board of Education will name its new Superintendent. Trustees will vote on the appointment in closed session and make an announcement at their regular board meeting tonight at 6:30 pm. Head to the district website and board agenda for details on how to listen in via Zoom. A press release will follow the announcement.
Link to agenda: https://santabarbara.novusagenda.com/AgendaPublic/

***

El dia de hoy, el Consejo de Educación del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Santa Bárbara nombrará a su nuevo superintendente. Los miembros del Consejo votarán sobre dicho nombramiento en sesión cerrada, y anunciarán su decisión en la sesión de Consejo regular el dia de hoy a las 6:30 pm. Por favor diríjase al sitio web del distrito y consulte el orden del día para obtener detalles acerca de cómo escuchar por medio de Zoom. Un comunicado de prensa se hará público después del anuncio.

Enlace al orden del día: https://santabarbara.novusagenda.com/AgendaPublic/

Maria Larios-Horton is at Santa Barbara Unified School District.
March 29 at 5:03 PM · Santa Barbara, CA ·

** Attention families with students in SB Unified’s Secondary Schools:

Remote learning ready for launch!

- ‪Monday, March 30‬ and ‪Tuesday, March 31‬ will function as Teacher Work Days
- ‪Wednesday, April 1‬ will function as our first day of a new kind of school.
- We will communicate procedures for collecting any necessary items from school, such as devices, instruments, or personal items.

Today introduces our SBUnified Looped In Podcast, created by Gina Pearce and Rob Cooper, SBUnified Technology Integration Support Specialists. post_text:
San Marcos, Santa Barbara, and Dos Pueblos high school Mock Trial teams are progressing into the next round of the 37th annual Mock Trial competition, to be held today, Saturday, February 29, at the Santa Barbara County Courthouse. The semi-final round of the competition begins at 9 a.m. followed by the finals at 1 p.m. The awards ceremony will be hosted by Judge Brian Hill between 4-4.30 p.m. at the Courthouse in Department 2.

The Mock Trial competition provides an educational opportunity, immersing high school students in key concepts of the law, the legal process, and our justice system. High school teams simulate a civic or criminal trial with attorneys and witnesses, learn how to construct a convincing and compelling case, and respond to legal arguments with competence and confidence.

The winner of the local competition will represent Santa Barbara County at the State Mock Trial competition in Los Angeles, March 20-22.

The competition is sponsored by the Santa Barbara County Education Office, the Santa Barbara County Superior Court, and the Constitutional Rights Foundation.

Santa Barbara Unified School District leaders have assembled a group of community members, parents, educators and other stakeholders to develop a Comprehensive Plan for Multilingual Pathways.

The Global California 2030 initiative challenges state schools to develop opportunities for students to acquire multiple languages that will prepare them for the 21st century economy, broaden their perspective and understanding of the world, and strengthen the diversity of backgrounds and languages that make California’s culture and economy vibrant and dynamic.

Read more about this story on the district website: https://www.sbunified.org/2019/08/30/community-leaders-join-santa-barbara-unified-school-district-in-developing-plan-for-multilingual-pathways/

La escuela comienza el 20 de agosto! Aparte de la fecha del primer día de escuela, la otra fecha importante a anotar en sus calendarios es la de las Noches de regreso a la escuela. ¿No tiene claro cuándo es la noche de regreso a la escuela en la escuela de su hijo? Les tenemos la respuesta, ya que tenemos esa información publicada en nuestra página web: www.sbunified.org

¿Por qué es importante asistir a la Noche de regreso a la escuela? Este evento ofrece a los padres la oportunidad de obtener información importante sobre la experiencia educativa de sus hijos. Venga a visitar la escuela de su hijo, conozca a sus maestros y descubra formas de apoyar la educación de su hijo.

Todos los eventos contarán con servicios de interpretación al español.

#SBUnified
#SBUnifiedBack2School
#SantaBarbara
#Goleta

It’s August and school starts on August 20! Besides the first day of school, the next important date to mark on your calendar is back to school night. Not sure when the back to school night event is for your child’s school? We’ve got you covered and posted that information on our website: www.sbunified.org.

Why is it important to attend a back to school night? This event is an opportunity for all parents to learn important information about their child's educational experience. Come visit your student’s school, meet teachers, and discover ways to support your child.

Spanish language interpretation services will be available at all events.

#SBUnified
#SBUnifiedBack2School
#SantaBarbara

post_text: El primer día de clase es el 20 de agosto, y ya es hora de completar el proceso de inscripción anual. Las familias de alumnos nuevos y de los que continúan pueden inscribirse en el portal de Aeries del distrito, nuestro sistema de información estudiantil. Para empezar accedan a su cuenta del portal de Aeries visitando www.sbunified.org/aeries. RECORDATORIO IMPORTANTE - TODOS los alumnos, aunque se hayan inscrito para el año escolar anterior, deben estar inscritos antes de comenzar este nuevo año escolar. Los alumnos no podrán recibir sus programas de clases ni se les podrán asignar maestros en agosto hasta que se haya completado el proceso de inscripción. Recomendamos que se inscriban ahora, en julio, en caso de que se presente algún problema o que tengan una pregunta. Les tomará de 3 a 5 minutos para completar el proceso de inscripción en línea de su hijo/a. Si necesistan más información, por favor pónganse en contacto con la escuela de su estudiante.

post_text: The first day of school - August 20 - is just around the corner. It’s time to complete your annual registration process. The entire process can be completed in about 3-5 minutes, entirely online. Families of new and returning students can register online through Santa Barbara Unified’s Aeries Portal, our student information system. To get started, log into your Aeries Portal account by visiting: www.sbunified.org/aeries. IMPORTANT REMINDER - ALL students, regardless of registration in the previous school year, must be registered before they can start the new school year. Students will not receive their class schedules or teacher assignments until their registrations are complete. Please connect with your school site if you have any questions or need further support.

The Santa Barbara Unified School District is pleased to announce the selection of Cailean Kilroy Villaseñor as the new Assistant Principal at Santa Barbara High School. Many Dons may recognize a familiar face in Villaseñor, who has taught physical and life sciences at Santa Barbara Junior High since 2012, while also serving as the district’s Secondary Technology Integration Coach since 2017.

El Distrito Escolar Unificado de Santa Bárbara se complace en anunciar el nombramiento de Cailean Kilroy Villaseñor como la nueva subdirectora de Santa Barbara High School. Muchos Dons quizá reconozcan el rostro conocido de la Sra. Villaseñor, quien impartió clases de ciencias físicas y ciencias biológicas en Santa Barbara Junior High desde el 2012. Asimismo, trabajó en el distrito como especialista de apoyo para la integración de la tecnología de secundaria/preparatoria desde el 2017.

Visit the district website to read more about our newest Assistant Principal: https://www.sbunified.org/2019/07/19/cailean-kilroy-villasenor-named-assistant-principal-of-santa-barbara-high/

With this year’s celebratory theme of “Building Bridges”, the District’s English Learner Advisory Committee (DELAC) honored students, parents and educators at a special dinner celebration to recognize emerging multilingual students and their adult support system. Students were nominated by their schools for their effort and overall academic achievement while also overcoming personal challenges. Adults were also recognized for their work in going above and beyond in their support of students learning English.

Con el tema de celebración “Construyendo Puentes”, El Comité asesor de alumnos que aprenden inglés del distrito (DELAC) homenajeó a alumnos, padres y maestros durante una cena especial para celebrar y reconocer a los nuevos alumnos multilingües y a los maestros por su apoyo. Los alumnos fueron nombrados por sus escuelas, por sus esfuerzos y en general por sus logros académicos y por superar sus retos personales. Los adultos también fueron reconocidos por sus labores que van más allá del apoyo a los alumnos que aprenden inglés.
text:
With this year’s celebratory theme of “Building Bridges”, the District’s English Learner Advisory Committee (DELAC) honored students, parents and educators at a special dinner celebration to recognize emerging multilingual students and their adult support system. Students were nominated by their schools for their effort and overall academic achievement while also overcoming personal challenges. Adults were also recognized for their work in going above and beyond in their support of students learning English.

Con el tema de celebración “Construyendo Puentes”, El Comité asesor de alumnos que aprenden inglés del distrito (DELAC) homenajeó a alumnos, padres y maestros durante una cena especial para celebrar y reconocer a los nuevos alumnos multilingües y a los maestros por su apoyo. Los alumnos fueron nombrados por sus escuelas, por sus esfuerzos y en general por sus logros académicos y por superar sus retos personales. Los adultos también fueron reconocidos por sus labores que van más allá del apoyo a los alumnos que aprenden inglés.

post_text: Congrats to Royals Camille Lubach and Emma Tracewell for winning awards at the SB Arts Association Student Art Fund Grandparent Portrait Show!
shared_text:
San Marcos Royals
April 14, 2019 at 7:38 PM ·

Congrats to Camille Lubach who won the SB Art Association Best in Show Award at the Student Art Fund Grandparent Portrait show. Her Oil painting, titled "Grandpa in Uniform" is of her Grandfather in his train conductor hat (he was a train conductor for the zoo) and garnered her a $450 prize.

Also congrats to Emma Tracewell who won the Last Arcada Plaza Award for her piece of digital art entitled "Mamau's Apple Pie Recipe." (Hint - look at the writing behind her grandmother)

You can view their work in the Faulkner Gallery at the downtown SB Public Library through April 30th.
